This is an observational, multicenter, single arm, prospective study to evaluate safety and tolerability of selective and ultraselective drug eluting beads transcatheter intraarterial chemoembolization (DEB-TACE) with up to 3 ml of well calibrated 100 mu microspheres and up to 150 mg of doxorubicin, for the treatment of non resectable hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC).

 The hypothesis is that 100 mu beads penetrate deeper into the tumor than those eluting beads with larger volumes without increasing the risk and complications of DEB-TACE.

